
Useful flags:

- DEBUG=1 - Does several things:
  - Builds with debug flags: -Os -g3
  - Enables asserts and logging output
  - Switches to BUILDDIR=build_dbg

- PRECISE=1 - Enables precise mode, by default things are imprecise for
  faster dev time:
  - 1M benches: 10 minutes -> 1 hour
  - 1G benches: 1 hour -> 1 day
  - Some other flags such as SKIP_WARMUP are set in cases where they
    shouldn't matter

- THUMB=1 - Switches to thumb mode:
  - Cross-compiles with arm-linux-gnueabi-gcc -mthumb -march=armv7 --static
  - Runs benches under qemu-arm
  - Note this is slow!

Bugs:

- Sometimes littlefs2 returns garbage in lfs2_fs_traverse. Probably a bug.

- Sometimes littlefs2 just breaks when creating many files. Not sure why.

- yaffs2 does not work with >=1MiB block sizes for some reason, errors
  with ENOSPC (twisted internally to EINVAL?). Note sure why.

- yaffs2 keeps track of all files (not just opened ones) with a linked-list
  that makes many testing grow O(n^2). This makes many benchmarking
  extremely slow and doesn't trigger an early exit because we ignore CPU
  time.

Runtime:

- time ( THUMB=1 make -f Makefile_1M plot-p26-wt )

  real    547m4.922s
  user    4644m37.692s
  sys     2m22.246s

- time ( THUMB=1 make -f Makefile_1M plot-p26-wt )

